"""
🔒 SECURITY BEST PRACTICES:

1. NEVER commit your HF_TOKEN to Git!
   - Add to .gitignore: echo "*.token" >> .gitignore
   - Use environment variables instead

2. Use "Write" access tokens only when uploading
   - Create at: https://huggingface.co/settings/tokens
   - Revoke after uploading if needed

3. Keep model private if trained on proprietary data
   - private=True ensures only you can access

4. Store token securely:
   - Environment variable: export HF_TOKEN=your_token
   - Or use: huggingface-cli login (stores in ~/.huggingface/token)

5. Check what's being uploaded:
   - Review files in ./ipl_cricket_lora before upload
   - Make sure no sensitive data in training logs
"""


# ============================================================================
# TROUBLESHOOTING
# ============================================================================

"""
❌ Common Issues and Solutions:

1. "Invalid token" error
   → Create new token at: https://huggingface.co/settings/tokens
   → Make sure "Write" permission is checked

2. "Repository not found" when downloading
   → You must login with token that has access to private repo
   → Use: huggingface-cli login

3. Files too large (>5GB)
   → Use Git LFS (automatically handled by huggingface_hub)
   → Or upload in chunks using upload_file() instead

4. Upload stuck/slow
   → Check your internet connection
   → Try uploading individual files first for testing

5. "403 Forbidden" error
   → Token doesn't have write access
   → Repo belongs to organization you don't have access to
"""


